## Multiple Linear Regression

The dataset was partitioned into training and validation sets (40 percent training). Model performance was evaluated using standard regression metrics.

### Initial Regression Results
- RMSE: 0.7560  
- MAE: 0.6252  
- MAPE: 231.0998  

### Regularized Regression Comparison
Ridge, Lasso, and Bayesian Ridge were tested. Ridge Regression performed best:

- RMSE: 0.7044  
- MAE: 0.5743  
- MPE: -129.6866  
- MAPE: 363.5149  

### Conclusion
Ridge Regression is the recommended model for 7-day forecasting, supporting inventory and pricing adjustments.

---

## Time Series Analysis

A series of smoothing and forecasting methods were evaluated:

- 7-day moving average  
- 30-day moving average  
- 7-day weighted moving average  
- Exponential smoothing (alpha = 0.2)  
- Linear regression trend model  

### Error Metrics Evaluated
- MAPE  
- MAE  
- MSE  
- RMSE  

### Findings
The simple 7-day moving average consistently produced the lowest error across all metrics, making it the most reliable method for weekly forecasting.

### Conclusion
The 7-day moving average is recommended for short-term operational planning due to its simplicity, interpretability, and accuracy.

---

## Final Recommendation

Use Ridge Regression and the 7-day moving average for weekly forecasting of bike rental demand. Avoid long-term forecasting (30 days or more) due to declining model accuracy.

